    "overview_number": 1,
    "overview_title": "Drum Roll, Please!",
    "overview_subtitle": "Volume of a Cylinder",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students develop the formula for a cylinder's volume by visualizing its volume as a stack of congruent disks and multiplying the base area and height. They use the formula to calculate the volume or radius length. Students apply the same volume formula for oblique cylinders."
  },
