      "overview_item_content_type": "html",
      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "A cylinder is a three-dimensional object with two parallel, congruent circular bases.",
          "You can derive the formula for a cylinder's volume by modifying the formula for a right rectangular prism's volume.",
          "The formula for the volume of a cylinder is <math><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Ï€</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math>, where <math><mi>V</mi></math> is the volume, <math><mi>r</mi></math> is the length of the radius of the base, and <math><mi>h</mi></math> is the height.",
          "An oblique cylinder is a cylinder in which the bases are parallel to each other, but they are not aligned directly above or below each other.",
          "The volume formula for an oblique cylinder is the same as the volume formula for a right cylinder."
        ]
      }
    },
